1. Nf3 g6 2. c4 Bg7 3. d4 f5 4. Nc3 Nf6 5. g3 O-O 6. Bg2 d6 7. O-O c6 8. Re1 { If white gets to play e4 he will be very happy as the e6 square and the e7 pawn can become weak } (8. d5 { is the main line. Ive played it a couple of times as black. Don't really like White. } 8... e5) 8... Ne4 9. Qd3 Nxc3 10. bxc3 e5 11. e4 fxe4 (11... d5!? 12. cxd5 cxd5) 12. Qxe4 Bf5 13. Qe2 Nd7 14. Ba3 { Attacks and pins the weakness on d6. } { [%csl Gd6] } 14... Qe7 (14... Qc7 { Might be more accurate as it avoids the annoying pins. }) 15. Rad1 { I didn't find Nxe5 which seems to be strong. Rad1 develops the last piece and puts even more pressure on blacks central pawns. } { [%csl Gd6] } (15. Nxe5! Rae8 (15... Nxe5 16. f4) 16. Qd2 Qd8 17. Bxd6 Nxe5 18. dxe5 Bxe5 19. c5) 15... Rad8 { I didn't find Nxe5 which seems to be strong. Rad1 develops the last piece and } (15... c5) 16. h3 { I wanted to stop Bg4 in some dxe5 lines. I found it annoying after 15.dxe5 Nxe5 16.c5 Bg4. } (16. dxe5 Nxe5 17. c5 Bg4 { This is the reason I played 16.h3. }) 16... g5 (16... c5 { Might have been a better option. } 17. dxe5 dxe5 18. Bc1 $14 { Looks strong. White has a monster bishop on g2, a nice outpost on d5 and some pressure against e5. At the same time his queenside structure is ruined. } { [%cal Gc1g5,Gg2d5] }) 17. dxe5 (17. Qb2 { Was another possibility. } 17... b6 18. dxe5 Nxe5 19. Nxe5 Bxe5 20. f4! $18 { [%cal Ge1e7] }) 17... Nxe5 18. c5! { Was my idea. Blacks pieces seem to be overloaded. } 18... g4 { According to the engine this is a mistake. But I think blacks position is hopeless no matter what. } (18... Nxf3+ 19. Qxf3 Qf6 (19... Qd7 20. Rxd6 { The engine must be high or something. There is no way this isn't winning for white. } 20... Rde8 { Maybe the engine is right . Black has some compensation in form of stronger bishops and whites broken pawn chain on the queenside. } 21. Re3 Qf7 { [%csl Ga2,Gc3,Gc5] } 22. Bc1 Rxe3 23. Bxe3 Qxa2 24. Qh5 h6 25. Bd4 { I have no idea whats going on here. Black has a passed pawn but whites pieces are getting active. Blacks king side might experience some issues. } 25... Qf7 26. Qd1 a5 27. Bf1 Be6) 20. cxd6 Qxc3 21. d7 Qxf3 22. Bxf3 Rxd7 23. Bxf8 Bxf8 24. Re5 $18) 19. cxd6 Nxf3+ $7 (19... gxf3 20. dxe7 fxe2 21. Rxd8 $18) 20. Bxf3 Qxe2 21. Bxe2 Bxc3 22. Bc4+ Kh8 23. d7! { White is winning material. The simple threat of Bxf8 and Be7 is impossible to stop. } 23... Bxe1 (23... b5 24. Bxf8 bxc4 (24... Bxe1 25. Be7 { [%cal Ge7f6,Ge7d8] }) 25. Re8) 24. Bb2+ 1-0


